---
import StackLayout from '../layouts/StackLayout.astro';

const a11yDate = '2026-05-17';
---
<StackLayout
  title="About — Stack"
  description="About Stack: a minimal-brutalist workout tracker concept by dcrader.dev. Includes accessibility statement."
  active="about"
>
  {/* Hero */}
  <section class="block-border-b bg-stack-bone">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-14 sm:py-20">
      <p class="tag text-stack-red">/ABOUT</p>
      <h1 class="display text-7xl sm:text-8xl lg:text-9xl mt-3 leading-[0.85]">
        Sets, reps,<br/>
        load &mdash; <span class="text-stack-red">that's it.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-stack-graphite text-lg">
        Stack is a concept site for a workout tracker that does one thing: log what you lifted.
        No social feed, no streak shaming, no AI form coach.
        Just a clean grid of sets, reps, and load &mdash; and the numbers going up over time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Principles */}
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <h2 class="tag text-stack-red">/PRINCIPLES</h2>
    <ol class="mt-6 space-y-6">
      <li class="grid sm:grid-cols-[3rem_1fr] gap-4">
        <span class="numeral text-5xl text-stack-red">01</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="display text-3xl">The bar is the source of truth.</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-stack-graphite">No estimated calories, no recovery scores, no &ldquo;readiness&rdquo; nonsense. If you put it on the bar and stood up with it, that's the data.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="grid sm:grid-cols-[3rem_1fr] gap-4">
        <span class="numeral text-5xl text-stack-red">02</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="display text-3xl">A workout is a list. Treat it like one.</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-stack-graphite">Vertical grid, big numerals, no clever animations. The app should disappear between sets, not perform for you.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="grid sm:grid-cols-[3rem_1fr] gap-4">
        <span class="numeral text-5xl text-stack-red">03</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="display text-3xl">Build the block, then run the block.</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-stack-graphite">Programs are blocks. Six to twelve weeks. You don't redesign your training plan in the middle of a set &mdash; you finish the block and decide afterwards.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  {/* Stack vs. the rest */}
  <section class="bg-stack-paper block-border-t block-border-b">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
      <h2 class="tag text-stack-red">/WHAT IT ISN'T</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-0 block-border">
        <div class="p-6 sm:border-r-2 border-b-2 sm:border-b-0 border-stack-ink">
          <p class="display text-2xl text-stack-red">NOT</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-stack-graphite">
            <li>&times; A social network for your gym</li>
            <li>&times; An AI form coach</li>
            <li>&times; A streak counter</li>
            <li>&times; A subscription with three tiers</li>
            <li>&times; A wearable companion app</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 bg-stack-bone">
          <p class="display text-2xl">IS</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-stack-graphite">
            <li>&check; A logbook that opens fast</li>
            <li>&check; Sets, reps, and load in a grid</li>
            <li>&check; A rest timer that doesn't nag</li>
            <li>&check; PR tracking with e1RM</li>
            <li>&check; A weekly plan you can actually read</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Accessibility */}
  <section id="accessibility" class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <p class="tag text-stack-red">/ACCESSIBILITY STATEMENT</p>
    <h2 class="display text-5xl sm:text-6xl mt-2">Built to be read.</h2>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-stack-graphite max-w-3xl">
      <p>
        Stack is committed to meeting <strong>WCAG 2.1 Level AA</strong> as a minimum standard.
        That means high-contrast text, visible focus rings, semantic markup, keyboard-navigable
        interactions, and large hit targets.
      </p>
      <p>
        The site uses condensed display type for headings and a neutral sans for body copy.
        All numerals are tabular so loads and rep counts line up cleanly when scanned.
        Color is never the only signal &mdash; PR rows have both a red border <em>and</em> a label.
      </p>
      <h3 class="display text-2xl text-stack-ink mt-6">Found a barrier?</h3>
      <p>
        If anything on this site is hard to read, hear, or operate, please tell us.
        We treat accessibility bugs the same as functional bugs &mdash; they get fixed,
        not deprioritized.
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
        <li>
          <span class="tag text-stack-concrete mr-2">EMAIL</span>
          <a class="underline hover:text-stack-red" href="mailto:accessibility@stack.dcrader.dev">
            accessibility@stack.dcrader.dev
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="tag text-stack-concrete mr-2">UPDATED</span>
          <time datetime={a11yDate} class="numeral">{a11yDate}</time>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="display text-2xl text-stack-ink mt-6">Known limitations</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
        <li>This is a concept/demo site. The rest-timer controls are visual mocks &mdash; they don't
          run a real timer yet. Once interactive, they'll include audible and visual cues plus a
          <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> path.</li>
        <li>Some marketing copy uses tight tracking on extra-large display type. This is intentional
          for the brutalist aesthetic, but if it harms readability for you, please report it.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Closing */}
  <section class="bg-stack-ink text-stack-bone">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
      <p class="tag text-stack-red-bright">/CREDITS</p>
      <h2 class="display text-4xl sm:text-5xl mt-2 max-w-3xl">
        A concept by <a href="https://dcrader.dev" class="underline hover:text-stack-red-bright">dcrader.dev</a> &mdash;
        part of a series of focused, single-purpose tools.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-stack-rebar-soft max-w-2xl">
        Built with Astro &amp; Tailwind. Deployed on Vercel. No tracking, no third-party scripts,
        no &ldquo;cookie consent&rdquo; banner because there's nothing to consent to.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</StackLayout>
